</question-stem>
<answer-choice-set>
<answer-choice correct="yes"> They were bought by a wide variety of educated
people.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> They were bought only by the very rich.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> They were bought mainly by professional musicians.</answer-choice>
<answer-choice> They were bought mostly for display purposes.</answer-choice>
</answer-choice-set>
<explanation interaction="true">
<para>  The professor says that Petrucci's editions were <emphasis emphasis-type="italic"> within
the means, </emphasis>which means affordable, for gentry, merchants and artisans,
so you<emphasis emphasis-type="italic">  c</emphasis>an infer that this comprises
a broad range of educated people. The<emphasis emphasis-type="italic"></emphasis>other
three options contradict this fact because they are too narrow<emphasis emphasis-type="italic"></emphasis>in
scope.</para>
